data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527308\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ety1665702780801.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ety1665702780801.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ety1665702780801.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ety1665702780801\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                        \n Migration of Global Constants\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ety1665702780801__p_d68636e1_d68637e1_d68638e1\">In Uniface 9 global constants were defined as global objects in a dedicated editor. In Uniface 10, they are defined in a reserved IncludeScript called <code class=\"ph codeph\">DEFPARAM</code> using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">#define</span> directive.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ety1665702780801__p_d68639e1_d68640e1_d68641e1\">Uniface automatically migrates global constants to an IncludeScript library, but the change in the way they are defined affects the way you subsequently export global constants.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ety1665702780801__p_d68642e1_d68643e1_d68644e1\">It is no longer possible to specify <code class=\"ph codeph\">constants</code> as an object type for export in the Export form or using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$ude (\"export\")</span>. Consequently:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ety1665702780801__li_d31346e1_d31347e1_d31348e1\">Exporting all objects in an IncludeScript library also exports the global constants in <code class=\"ph codeph\">DEFPARAM</code>.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ety1665702780801__li_d31349e1_d31350e1_d31351e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ety1665702780801__p_d68645e1_d68646e1_d68647e1\">When using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$ude(\"export\")</span>, you will need to use the following syntax in Uniface 10:</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ety1665702780801__p_d68648e1_d68649e1_d68650e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">$ude(\"export\", \"library<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>include\", \"DEFPARM\",</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">ExportFile</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">, \"library=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Library</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\")</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ety1665702780801__p_d68651e1_d68652e1_d68653e1\">The equivalent Uniface 9 command no longer works:</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ety1665702780801__p_d68654e1_d68655e1_d68656e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">$ude(\"export\", \"library<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>constants\", \"<span class=\"ph gold\">*</span>\",</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">ExportFile</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">, library=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Library</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\")</code>\n</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527308\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527308\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Migration of Global Constants Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Migration of Global Constants In Uniface 9 global constants were defined as global objects in a dedicated editor. In Uniface 10, they are defined in a reserved IncludeScript called DEFPARAM using the #define directive. Uniface automatically migrates global constants to an IncludeScript library, but the change in the way they are defined affects the way you subsequently export global constants. It is no longer possible to specify constants as an object type for export in the Export form or using $ude (\"export\") . Consequently: Exporting all objects in an IncludeScript library also exports the global constants in DEFPARAM . When using $ude(\"export\") , you will need to use the following syntax in Uniface 10: $ude(\"export\", \"library ; include\", \"DEFPARM\", ExportFile , \"library= Library \") The equivalent Uniface 9 command no longer works: $ude(\"export\", \"library ; constants\", \" * \", ExportFile , library= Library \") Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}